OL,3,CHome Office sacks chief immigration
OL,4,Cinspector after airport security row
OL,6,FThe immigration minister Tom Pursglove
OL,7,Fsaid the Home Office "categorically
OL,8,Frejects" the claims.
OL,10,FResponding to an urgent question from
OL,11,FLabour in the Commons, Mr Pursglove
OL,12,Fsaid: "When it comes to the questions
OL,13,Fthat she raises around these flights
OL,14,Fat London City airport and the
OL,15,Finformation that has been put in the
OL,16,Fpublic domain, the Home Office
OL,17,Fcategorically rejects these claims by
OL,18,FDavid Neal."
OL,20,FLabour branded the move "total Tory
OL,21,Fchaos on borders and immigrations".
