OL,3,CHome Office sacks chief immigration
OL,4,Cinspector after airport security row
OL,6,FMr Pursglove insisted Border Force
OL,7,Fperformed "checks on 100% of scheduled
OL,8,Fpassengers arriving in the UK and risk-
OL,9,Fbased intelligence-led checks on
OL,10,Fgeneral aviation."
OL,12,FHe added: "Mr Neal was made aware of a
OL,13,Fspecific issue in the recording of
OL,14,Fdata at London City airport which
OL,15,Fmeant that a large proportion of
OL,16,Fflights recorded as high-risk should
OL,17,Fhave been reclassified as low-risk,
OL,18,Fand it's disappointing that he's
OL,19,Fchosen to put misleading data into the
OL,20,Fpublic domain."
